# Token Economy Rules

- Keep responses concise.
- Do not summarize entire files unless asked.
- Do not paste large code blocks when a small diff or focused snippet is enough.
- Read only files directly relevant to the task.
- Avoid broad searches across the repo unless the first targeted search fails.
- Prefer editing existing functions over creating new layers.
- Ask for clarification only when the implementation would otherwise be unsafe or likely wrong.
- Do not explain obvious code. Explain only tradeoffs, risks, or non-obvious decisions.